Egg (
Figs. 24J–K
): Small (overall length 
2.6 mm
), ovoid with dorsal surface of capsule much more convex than ventral surface and almost round in cross-section; about 1.4x longer than wide. Anterior portion somewhat narrowed. Capsule surface very minutely and evenly granulose. Micropylar plate elongate, about ¾ the length of capsule with posterior half slightly widened and posterior end indented; open interiorly. Micropylar cup distinct. Operculum almost circular and strongly raised and with a small, blackish, knob-like capitulum in centre.

